The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Thursday, August 12, 2004 				 US plans Najaf assault
																								Najaf, Aug. 11 (Reuters): US Marines said today they were preparing a final assault on Iraqi Shia militia in Najaf, after a radical cleric ordered his men to keep fighting even if he was killed.																								The New York Times said that after preparing for a major attack on militia loyal to cleric Moqtada al-Sadr in Najaf today, US forces called it off as it was about to begin. 																								But it said officers described the move as a postponement and said the attack could go ahead any time. 																								Thousands of Sadrs supporters vented their anger against interim Prime Minister Iyad Allawi in Nassiriya and several other cities.																								In Nassiriya demonstrators torched Allawis political party office and called for his downfall. 
